title: Balanced mind states, familiar in sequence, becomes strange in parallel.
pid: d63c3355-303a-424e-bf90-a31071388be5
body: |2-
  It's common to balance (consciously or not)
    one's own processing across time of different states of mind
    such as [[id:48ca133b-8986-483c-8d47-b8a64213b571][the examples]].
  Differently,
    an objective observer or simulator -- both godlike conceptions --
    world would have to dedicate processing between such states in parallel.
